# ─── Discord ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# From https://discord.com/developers/applications
DISCORD_TOKEN=your-bot-token
DISCORD_CLIENT_ID=your-application-id
# One or more guild (server) ids, COMMA-SEPARATED. Slash commands register
# instantly to each listed guild (great for a cluster of union servers, or fast
# dev iteration). Leave unset to register globally (all servers, up to ~1h).
#   e.g. DISCORD_GUILD_ID=111111111111111111,222222222222222222
DISCORD_GUILD_ID=your-guild-id
# One or more Discord user ids (COMMA-SEPARATED) who are bot admins — they can
# run admin commands (/config, /sync) in ANY server regardless of their roles.
# BOT_ADMIN_ID=111111111111111111
# Optional: one or more role ids (COMMA-SEPARATED) whose holders count as bot
# admins for /config and /sync — useful in a server where you lack Manage Server
# but can be given a "Bot Admin" role. (Command *visibility* is still controlled
# by Discord; see the admin-command notes.)
# BOT_ADMIN_ROLE_ID=333333333333333333

# ─── NIKKE news auto-timestamp ──────────────────────────────
# Preferred setup is per-server: an admin runs `/config news #channel` (repeat
# for multiple channels). This env var is an optional GLOBAL FALLBACK, added to
# whatever a server configured — COMMA-SEPARATED for several channels. For each
# embed posted in a watched channel, the bot reads the text and replies with a
# <t:…> timestamp. Times with no stated zone are assumed UTC+9 (edit
# DEFAULT_OFFSET_MINUTES in apps/bot/src/events/messageCreate.ts to change).
# NIKKE_NEWS_CHANNEL_ID=1038676900081565736,1234567890123456789

# ─── Gacha event ingestion (LLM parse; operator-approve) ───
# All optional. The announcement→event parser calls an OpenAI-compatible
# /chat/completions endpoint (e.g. a local llama.cpp server). Proposals are
# stored for review; NOTHING reaches the calendar without /events approval.
# Smoke-test the endpoint first: npm run smoke:gacha -- path/to/notice.txt
#
# Master switch: announcement ingestion is OFF unless this is set (so a deploy
# without a reachable LLM endpoint never spends calls or logs errors). When on,
# posts in the watched news channels that carry an event time are parsed and a
# proposal row is stored for /events review.
# GACHA_INGEST_ENABLED=1
# GACHA_LLM_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8770/v1
# GACHA_LLM_MODEL=local
# Completion budget: clamped UP to 16000 (smaller budgets truncate real
# patch notes mid-JSON — see apps/bot/src/lib/gacha/ingest.ts MIN_MAX_TOKENS).
# GACHA_LLM_MAX_TOKENS=16000
# GACHA_LLM_TEMPERATURE=0.4
# GACHA_LLM_TIMEOUT_MS=600000

# ─── Patch notes ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional. Channel id where Maiden posts patch notes on deploy. When the top
# entry in apps/bot/src/patchNotes.ts has a version that hasn't been posted yet,
# the bot announces it here once. Leave unset to disable.
# PATCH_NOTES_CHANNEL_ID=1234567890123456789

# ─── Database ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# On Railway, DATABASE_URL is injected automatically (internal host, only
# reachable inside Railway). To run scripts/migrations from your OWN computer,
# set DATABASE_PUBLIC_URL to the Postgres service's PUBLIC connection string
# (Railway → Postgres → Connect). The code prefers the public URL off-Railway
# and the internal one on Railway, so you can paste both.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/bakery_bot
DATABASE_PUBLIC_URL=postgresql://user:password@your-db.proxy.rlwy.net:12345/railway

# ─── Feature requests → GitHub ──────────────────────────────
# Optional. If set, /feature-request also opens a GitHub issue. Without it,
# requests are still saved to the database. Token needs permission to create
# issues on the repo; GITHUB_REPO defaults to Infernal-Crack-LED/bakery-bot.
# GITHUB_TOKEN=github_pat_...
# GITHUB_REPO=Infernal-Crack-LED/bakery-bot

# ─── Web dashboard ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Public base url of the Next.js app (used for links/redirects)
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
